  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Abrupt onset of inflammation in the episclera\n70% of cases occurs in women (usually young/middle-aged)\nUsually a benign, self-limited condition\nCan be classified into simple (more common) or nodular types\nMost commonly idiopathic but may occur as an ocular manifestation of underlying autoimmune conditions eg\nRA\n,\nIBD\nAlso associated with\nglaucoma\nand cataracts\n[1]",
